    "summary": "I am a geologist by background. I have experience in roles as consultant, technical expert and researcher. I have expert knowledge of clastic sedimentology and reservoir architecture.  I also have significant experience in programming, software design and the application of GIS. \n\nMy analytical skills are particularly strong. I am an inquisitive, creative problem solver with an open mind and outstanding communicative skills. Despite my curiosity, I have a keen sense for scope and priority. I consider myself to be an excellent team player.\n\nI thrive in multidisciplinary teams, perform well under pressure and have always enjoyed teaching and supervising colleagues and students.\n\nSkills:\n- clastic sedimentology on all scales\n- sedimentary facies interpretation from log and core\n- applied sequence stratigraphy\n- reservoir characterisation and prediction\n- well correlation\n- play-based analysis/CRS mapping\n- risk and uncertainty analysis (Monte Carlo simulation)\n- basic petroleum systems modelling\n- 2D and 3D seismic interpretation and mapping\n- seismic attribute analysis\n- seismic geomorphology\n- ArcGIS, QGIS\n- data management\n- C, C++, Java, Object Pascal, VB, JavaScript, VBScript, Python and SQL. \n\nExperienced user of various technical applications, including Petrel, Landmark (OpenWorks and Decision Space Desktop), Kingdom, GeoX, Trinity, and ArcGIS. \n\nExperience in exploration and prospect evaluation in the North Sea, West of Shetland Basin, Norway, Greenland, North and West Africa (onshore and offshore), Black Sea and Caspian Sea.",
