                    "day": null,
                    "year": 2010
                },
                "end": {
                    "month": 6,
                    "day": null,
                    "year": 2011
                }
            },
            "description": "A regional evaluation of the petroleum potential of the NE Greenland margin, based on publicly available data and restricted data from the Geological Survey of Denmark and Greenland (GEUS). The regional geology was compared to that of the Norwegian Sea, which is the conjugate margin. The license blocks on offer in the 2012-2013 licensing round were ranked, and the minimum commercial field size for a standalone discovery was evaluated. ",
